cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and the use of large language models based on Transformer architecture. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning models for improving performance. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it deals with the task of stance detection, which is a subfield of information retrieval. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for improving performance.
